      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing, a parent's job is to protect their kids, and right now, i'm the one they need protection from. staying is just prolonging the inevitable struggle for them. if i actually loved them, wouldn't i want to remove the biggest obstacle to their happiness? it feels so much more logical to let them go so they can actually thrive without me constantly dragging them into my chaos.",
